President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation to honor the victims of the attack on police officers in Dallas, Texas. The proclamation orders that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff at the White House, public buildings, military posts, naval stations, and naval vessels until sunset on July 12, 2016. The flag will also be flown at half-staff at all United States embassies, consular offices, and other facilities abroad, including military facilities and naval vessels and stations.